name: Noor
review: I like the two heads of the pen and it lasts long time

name: chula
review: Everyday

name: Ash
review: I use the product to add a pop of colour. It is very bright and gives that extra eccentric touch.

name: fashionhydra
review: Love the sponge end for feathering the liner, but it's so soft I found it hard to keep neat.

name: LC
review: It does go on nice and smooth but smudges absolutely everywhere so quick. I had only put it on my top lid and it was half way down my cheeks. Probably one of the worst eyeliners I've ever used.

name: Tiff
review:
I got the blue and yellow liners and I love them! I hardly ever see drugstore brands have PIGMENTED pastels. I used these both on the upper lash line and waterline, the waterline only lasted about 4 1/2 hours. But they are so perfect for the upper lash line to give an extra pop of color, they lasted about 9 hours before smudging on my lid. Which is awesome, because I didn't use primer. (I consider my lids to be normal, not overly dry or oily.) The blue took only two swipes to be opaque and the yellow took three.

These are very comparable to Stila smudge sticks, only a little more creamy/smooth. I would love to see more colors with this particular liner.

name: Amber
review: I use this product everyday. Absolutely love the matte look of this product. Stays on all day long. I have this pencil in both brown and black.

name: saral
review: This is the one and only eyeliner pencil i have found that keeps my waterline rimmed! It also stays on my top lash line all day long.  I never leave reviews, but i am that confident about this eyeliner.

name: leighfost
review: I really like how creamy the pencil feels. Glides on.

name: BeetyBoop
review: I was hoping this would last as long as the Revlon Colorstay eyeliner (which I have used for yrs.) but this one doesn't.  It only lasted a couple hrs. then smudged and faded.

name: Eyes
review: Eyes. It's a liner. Also has a smug tip on opposite side of pencil.   It goes on smoothly holds pigment all day. Even on hot humid days

name: Chiby
review: 30 minutes after applied it looked like i cried. I don't recommend it at all

name: TP
review: I use blackest black colors for eyes on daily basis. Revlon was best pencil I used for over 15 years. Daily. But then, first, they kept making pencils shorter and shorter and each time more expensive. I still loved the color and kept buying. But now its nonsense. Among pencils there is no black, at most dark grey. I tried to add liner that they labeled blackest black, but it looks at best light gray or medium brown. Looks like I have to switch the company. Revlon, please get your blackest black pencils back.

name: Nova
review: I bought this to line my waterline and it was horrible! Within 10 minutes it was smudging at both corners of my eyes. Also it went on a nice dark black but immediately faded to a dark grey color. Very disappointed.

name: suze rn
review: pick it because of discount - but I would buy again

name: Pat
review: I use it for my eyebrows.

name: MishyMash
review: Purchased assuming that it was a twist up, I had planned on giving to a friend . . until I tried it.  It goes on smoothly, stays put all day long, doesn't irritate sensitive eyes, and the Marine Green looks amazing.  I actually repurchased a spare, along with a sharpener -- a very happy accident.

name: Amy
review: Love it

name: Kathy D
review: I need advice on the best way to trim it without it getting chewed up in the metal trimmer I use for my other pencils.

name: Monika the realtor
review: I have worn this as my daily eye liner for over 2 years.  I have brown/bluish timt eyes and somehow this works forme.  There is rarely a week that 2 or 3 people don't comment about how much they love this eye liner.  Occasionally I will switch to some other color and don't recall ever having received any comments on those!

name: Depaul
review: I have oily eyelids and most products will melt on my eyes and most primers won't do anything. I haven't used kajal eyeliners for years since they always smudged so badly on me. I decided to give this one a go since waterproof eyeliners that stay on well are hard to blend and won't give me a nice soft smokey look. It glides on, it's a beautiful shade of brown, not too ginger or too dark just perfect. It does fade throughout the day as anything will but considering my oily eyelids it performs really well.

name: Vic
review: Everyday or not, reaaally black and smooth!!

name: S
review: Easy to wash off

name: JVS
review: Purchased this as I was travelling, needed a liner, and my "go-to" was out of stock.

name: izzy
review: Love how is easy to apply.

name: Eli
review: I have oily skin so this product smears very easily.  Dont like at all.
